recommend check-in remains for M1, B3, and the TAME-supplement seating, unchanged. No further mechanical door remains open in the Nock/riscv64/rune thread this session has been walking -- the next real step in this specific area, if any, would itself open new design territory (a Hoon-to-Nock compiler front end, or a jet/acceleration layer), each meaningfully bigger than a single lap and worth its own check-in before starting.
